{
  "text": "Leaf expansion is the central process in which plants colonize space, and it is controlled by water and carbon availability [CITATION_1] . It represents the phase of the leaf's life span where the construction cost is paid [CITATION_2] . Leaf life span is a property of individual leaves [CITATION_3] . Despite low variation between short and long daylengths in the tropics, leaf fall in diverse species of this region is signalled by photoperiod [CITATION_4] , and its rate in those species is related to water availability [CITATION_5] .",
